data.title: 35 Famous People from Serbia
data.meta_description: Can you name 35 famous people from Serbia?
data.text:
Hint

Answer

Prince of Serbia who led Serbs in the Second Serbian uprising

Miloš Obrenović

The inventor of the modern electricity system

Nikola Tesla

Composer and most important figure of Serbian musical romanticism

Stevan Stojanović Mokranjac

One of the most important reformers of the modern Serbian language

Vuk Stefanović Karadžić

NBA player of LA Lakers, Sacramento and Charlotte

Vlade Divac

Medieval knight and the assassin of Sultan Murad

Miloš Obilić

Actor nicknamed "Bata", who acted in more than 340 films and TV series

Velimir Bata Živojinović

Bosnian-Serb who shot and killed Archduke Franz Ferdinand

Gavrilo Princip

Actor whose wife was the Serbian actress, Milena Dravić

Dragan Nikolić

Writer, philosopher, linguist and the first minister of education of Serbia

Dositej Obradović

Scientist and a founding member of NASA

Mihajlo Pupin

Defender who played for Manchester United from 2006 to 2014

Nemanja Vidić

Serbian President who resigned in 2000 and was arrested in 2001

Slobodan Milošević

NBA Most Valauble Player in 2021 and 2022 and champion in 2023

Nikola Jokić

Long time captain of the Yugoslavia national team, nicknamed "Piksi"

Dragan Stojković

Director of the movie Montevideo, God Bless You!

Dragan Bjelogrlić

Female long jumper, the 2023 World champion.

Ivana Vuleta

Female tennis who won 9 Grand Slam singles titles

Monika Seleš

Singer who won the 2007 Eurovision Song Contest

Marija Šerifović

Stage name of folk singer Svetlana Ražnatović

Ceca

Physicist and mathematician and the first wife of Albert Einstein

Mileva Marić

Author of comedies The Cabinet Minister's Wife and A Suspicious Person

Branislav Nušić

Basketball player who was NBA Champion and 3-time NBA All-Star

Predrag Stojaković

Serbian revolutionary who led the First Serbian Uprising

Karađorđe

First Archbishop of the autocephalous Serbian Church

Saint Sava

Conceptual and performance artist. Her work explores body, and feminist art

Marina Abramović

Climatologist who gave fundamental contributions to global science

Milutin Milanković

Director of movies Underground and Time of the Gypsies

Emir Kusturica

Novelist who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1961

Ivo Andrić

Writer and author of The Journal of Čarnojević and Migrations

Miloš Crnjanski

Female tennis player who was world No. 1 and who won French Open in 2008

Ana Ivanović
